articles.author: Vladimir Hedrih
articles.title: Women who rarely have sex are at an increased risk of dying, study finds - PsyPost
articles.description: Women who rarely have sex have a 70% higher mortality risk, and depressed individuals with infrequent sex have a 197% higher mortality risk compared to those with regular sexual activity.
articles.content: A recent study, based on data from the 20052010 National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES), has found that women who rarely engage in sexual activity have a 70% higher risk of dying co… [+5193 chars]
